# PART I — MAINSTREAM

## The 5‑Year Engineering Program

**Title:** Master of Engineering in ST‑T1024 Systems  
**Duration:** 5 Years (BEng + MEng)  
**Credits:** 300 ECTS (or equivalent)  
**Prerequisites:** Strong foundation in mathematics, physics, and programming  
**License:** Apache‑2.0 — Open curriculum for any university to adopt

---

### Year 1: Foundations (BEng Level 1)

| **Module** | **Content** | **Hours** |
|---|---|---|
| **Mathematics for Deterministic Systems** | Linear algebra, discrete mathematics, finite‑state theory | 60 |
| **Physics of Sensors and Actuators** | Thermodynamics, vibration, electromagnetism, signal fundamentals | 60 |
| **Introduction to Computer Architecture** | RISC‑V ISA, memory hierarchy, embedded systems basics | 60 |
| **Programming in C and Assembly** | Low‑level programming, memory management, bitwise operations | 60 |
| **Ethics and Sovereignty** | Geopolitics of AI, energy wall, data sovereignty, open standards | 30 |
| **Laboratory 1: Sensor Interfacing** | Connect sensors to microcontrollers, read data, calibrate | 60 |

**Year 1 Total: 330 hours**

